        <headline>Red Flag Warning issued June 7 at 2:04PM MDT until June 8 at 10:00PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>...ELEVATED FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS TODAY ARE EXPECTED TO RETURN
TOMORROW...

.DAYTIME LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY AND GUSTY WINDS WILL PERSIST
THROUGH SUNDAY.

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a Red Flag
Warning, which is in effect from 10 AM to 10 PM MDT Sunday.

* AFFECTED AREA...Fire weather zones 120 and 134.

* WIND...From the northwest at 25 to 30 mph with gusts up to 40
mph.

* HUMIDITY...As low as 18 percent.

* THUNDERSTORMS...Scattered thunderstorms are expected from mid-
day Saturday through the afternoon, mainly east of MT-Highway
24. No thunderstorms on Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Any fires that develop will likely spread rapidly
toward the southeast. Outdoor burning is not recommended.
</description>
        <instruction>Please advise the appropriate officials or fire crews in these
areas of this Red Flag Warning.</instruction>
